":"Shirland, Derbyshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Leigh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places (in at least sixteen counties, but especially Leigh in Lancashire) named either with the nominative case of Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’ (see   Lee  ) or with <i>lēage</i>, a late dative form of this word (see   Lye  ).","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 李, based on its Cantonese pronunciation. See   Li   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Leah","meanings":["English: variant of   Leigh  .","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surnames 李 and 利, see   Li   1 and 3."]},{"name":"Lee","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Sang, Jae, Jong, Jung, Sung, Yong, Kyung, Seung, Dong, Kwang, Myung.","English: topographic name for someone who lived near a meadow or a patch of arable land, Middle English <i>lee</i>, <i>lea</i>, from Old English <i>lēa</i>, dative case (used after a preposition) of <i>lēah</i>, which originally meant ‘wood or glade’.","English: habitational name from any of the many places in England named with Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘wood, glade’, including Lee in Buckinghamshire, Essex, Hampshire, Kent, and Shropshire, and Lea in Cheshire, Derbyshire, Herefordshire, Lancashire, Lincolnshire, and Wiltshire."]}]},{"name":"Nicole","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["feminine form of   Nicholas  , now also in frequent use throughout the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":30,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":39,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Nicole Leigh was born in 1185, in Northumberland, England, her father, Bartholomew de Leigh, was 29 and her mother, Emma Ruffus, was 24. She married Roger de Cauz in 1207, in Shirland, Derbyshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 1 April 1240, in Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1185–1 April 1240":"1185–1. aprill 1240","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1178–1219":"1178–1219","1208–1251":"1208–1251","1156–1217":"1156–1217","1161–1241":"1161–1241","1 April 1240":"1. aprill 1240","1241":"1241","1185":"1185","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1161":"1161","1181":"1181","Abt 1217":"umbes 1217","1217":"1217","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1156":"1156","1178":"1178","April 1240":"aprill 1240","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England":"Shalbourne, Wiltshire, England","Shalbourne, Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Shirland, Derbyshire, England":"Shirland, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"1185–1 April 1240":"1185–1. huhtikuuta 1240","1185–1240":"1185–1240","1178–1219":"1178–1219","1208–1251":"1208–1251","1156–1217":"1156–1217","1161–1241":"1161–1241","1 April 1240":"1. huhtikuuta 1240","1241":"1241","1185":"1185","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1161":"1161","1181":"1181","Abt 1217":"noin 1217","1217":"1217","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1156":"1156","1178":"1178","April 1240":"huhtikuu 1240","1208":"1208","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Shalbourne, Wiltsh